Solar Power Holding LLC is committed to the goal of producing 13 GWh of solar power annually in Italy.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Solar Power Holding LLC is committed to the goal of producing 13 GWh of solar power annually in Italy, realizing annual revenues of $4.54 million, and an annual rate of return of at least 14%. These business goals are attainable, since all of the key strategic positions for success – expertise, technologies, site advantages, and the energy market– are favorable.    Solar Power Holding, LLC was established on April 02, 2015 as an LLC with its registered office in Newark, Delaware (USA). The company will become active in the photo¬voltaics (PV) market in Italy. The key individual of the company is its CEO, Simon Grossgasteiger, who has many years of expertise and is fully familiar with the Italian market. To complement the company's core competencies, cooperation with the following two companies will be entered into: Windsolar GmbH, Italy, and Verotec GmbH, Italy.    Italy has the electric power market with the highest prices in Europe and is growing by 6 to 9% annually.    Solar Power Holding, LLC will acquire non-performing, undervalued operating companies of PV plants (mergers & acquisitions). Maintenance of the PV plants will be performed in cooperation with Windsolar GmbH and Verotec GmbH. The Italian Gestore Servizi Energetici (GSE) guarantees that it will purchase the power generated at set prices. Since existing PV plants are already connected to the grid and the purchase of the power is guaranteed, further measures for transferring the generated power or for distribution will not be required.    Non-performing, undervalued PV plant operating companies will be acquired, updated, and optimized. This is more profitable than building new plants. The acquisition will be performed in three steps: due diligence, acquisition, and updating and optimizing. A due diligence process has already been performed, and data are already present on operating companies that can be taken over.

Description: Experts in HUD's Fair Housing Complaint process; we help HOAs, landlords, & property managers avoid discrimination claims and suits.
Full Description: We are fair housing experts, not real estate attorneys coming to your property's defense after-the-fact. FHA’s experts filed several hundred fair housing complaints against apartments, HOAs, and condominium associations just like yours for violating the Fair Housing Act. Every single complaint filed with HUD against these properties was selected for investigation.  And almost every time, our fair housing complaint strategy compels the property to sign an agreement resulting in millions in total settlements. As a result of our experience defending consumers’ rights, we have become experts in the fair housing complaint process.  We understand the complete fair housing investigation cycle from complaint submission through investigation, negotiations, and settlement. Fair Housing Advocates, Inc. recently decided to dedicate its expertise to designing a comprehensive fair housing service made solely for landlords and property managers of rental and homeowners communities: The Fair Housing Property Pro. Our Fair Housing Property Pro seeks to empower homeowners associations [HOAs], condominiums, apartment communities, and mobile home parks by protecting their fair housing rights.  We provide exclusive knowledge about the fair housing complaint process only available from our insiders, so properties can avoid expensive fair housing discrimination claims long before they arise. We can help you protect your property.    We can help you know your fair housing rights. Reach us for a complimentary review of your property's Rules & Regulations- it's where we first looked when we filed against properties.

Description: HD Interactive is a developer of rich internet applications, including Flash, Flex, AIR, augmented reality and iPhone technologies.
Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: HD Interactive creates websites and web tools for a variety of clients. HDI specializes in Adobe Flash, Flex, and AIR solutions, Augmented Reality products, iPhone application development, and interactive training and entertainment.  Their team of professional designers and developers customizes every site to the client's specifications while utilizing SEO best practices.  HDI offers superb customer service and ensures the customer's satisfaction before completion of a project. One of HDI's latest ventures is [ChessJam](http://www.chessjam.com), an Adobe AIR chess game set in a 3D castle environment. Players can play timed games against robots or other ChessJammers from around the world. ChessJam's user count continues to grow as the application becomes more and more popular.  New live tournaments and leader boards have been added to increase friendly competition. HD Interactive has extensive experience working with Flash and Augmented Reality. HDI's latest in house Augmented Reality project is [Dr. Skully](http://www.drskully.com), the cool skull who lives in the Mirror of Misfotune. Dr. Skully was created as a way to showcase the capabilities of Augmented Reality while involving the user in more than the creation of a 3D object coming from an AR symbol. With Dr. Skully, you not only hold his horned head in your hands, he interacts with you, telling you your misfortunes in the areas of love, style, and more. To create Dr. Skully, HDI developers used an overlay over the webcam video for a grainy look and took advantage of new audio features in FlashPlayer 10 to sync his mouth movement with the audio clips. Become a fan of Dr. Skully on [Facebook](http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dr-Skullys-Mirror-of-Misfortune/283377004267?ref=ts) or Follow him on [Twitter](http://twitter.com/drSkullysMoM). To see Dr. Skully in action, click [here](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HxRaZekPofo). In 2008, HDI partnered up with Adobe to create [Tour de Flex](http://www.adobe.com/devnet/flex/tourdeflex/), a program that helps developers learn about the Flex programming language.  Tour de Flex shows examples of what Flex can do, complete with code, and programmers can browse to find help with a coding problem or learn about new web features Flex can be used for.  HDI and Adobe have continued to work together on other projects since Tour de Flex.

Description: TappedIn offers a platform that enables people to connect with the right people during events and conferences.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: TappedIn connects people so they can energize each other to achieve the growth we all want in our lives. It uses Human Energy to shift social actions. As technology advances and the digitization of our lives evolves, the need for face-to-face interaction and human-to-human connection continues to grow. Thousands of people attend hundreds of events each year in an attempt to be "connected" but are they really building meaningful relationships? The answer is no! Attending an event that results in zero conversations worth remembering turns out to be a waste of time, effort and money. What if people knew who they would meet at the event in advance, what they would talk about, and were actually prepared for every conversation they would have? TappedIn bridges the world of digital and in-person networking to help people create meaningful relationships that last a lifetime. In the future we plan to build in tools that will enable people to track follow through, manage relationships, and be focused on meeting the right people. So how does it work? Each attendee is matched with other attendees based on individual values and goals. 2 days before the event, they each get a list of people to meet and connect with. This way each attendee arrives at the event with a strong motivation to meet the 4-5 people they are perfectly matched with. Our Why-to-Why matching algorithm deciphers users' core beliefs and matches them with people that complement those core beliefs.
Industry Groups: Events, Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Messaging and Telecommunications, Software

Description: We are a modern innovative TPA providing fully outsourced claims services to the property and casualty insurance industry
Full Description: Alloy Claims is a Third-Party Administrator (TPA) built to service claims for insurance carriers, MGAs, self-insured entities, and fleets. Our principals have held senior leadership positions at large insurers in the USA and internationally. We know the impediments to modernizing claims organizations, and we know that the TPA market has not kept pace with innovations in the industry. We founded Alloy because we knew we could deliver better service & drive preferred cost outcomes while at the same time lowering loss adjustment expense.  We have partnerships with important industry leaders and service providers and we operate on a strict fee per claim model. There are no startup costs and no conflicts in our supply chain. We operate in a fully digitized environment with a transparent ecosystem. We use technology and automation to make our processes more efficient, but recognize the need for deeply experienced people to manage complex matters. Further, we support underwriting and actuarial needs by providing extensive data and analytics about loss experience to better inform risk selection and pricing decisions. Alloy can plug and play into any size organization and we provide the legitimacy and credibility needed to ensure your claims are managed efficiently, effectively, and accurately.
